"{\"uid\": \"thegatewaypundit.com-2024-08-olympics-pres-screen-men-science-tell-men-women\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Science has a foolproof way of telling you whether someone is a man or woman - chromosomes.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 91, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If they are XY, you are looking at a guy.\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 105, \"end\": 107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 0.9999668511610345, \"rank\": 3.314993790544621e-05, \"text\": \"XY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Apparently, that memo did not make its way over to the office of the International Olympic Committee President Thomas Bach, because he seemed to be a little more confused on the subject in recent comments.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 205, \"end\": 236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 247, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The comments came in response to Bach being pressed by a reporter on the female boxing controversy currently dominating Olympic discourse.\", \"from\": 343, \"to\": 481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 376, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999811784621, \"rank\": 1.882147962648599e-08, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two finalists in the women's boxing final, Algeria's Imane Khelif and Taiwan's Lin Yu-ting, failed a chromosome test last year, according to theInternational Boxing Association.\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 664, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 530, \"end\": 537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999982327237531, \"rank\": 1.704385746810997e-06, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9993154693228778, \"rank\": 0.0006413687965169683, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 645, \"end\": 651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.508472379464827e-16, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By implication, that suggests both tested positive for XY chromosomes, making them male.\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the credibility of the IBA has been called into question.\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 787, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.997686940878289, \"rank\": 0.0023184158937871115, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some mediaoutlets have reportedthat Khelif suffers from an incredibly rare medical condition known as \\\"Differences of Sex Development.\\\"\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Cleveland Clinicdefines DSD as \\\"conditions where a person's reproductive organs and genitals are 'mismatched' at birth.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland_Brown\", \"score\": 0.9999998373236981, \"rank\": 1.6267613487908177e-07, \"text\": \"Cleveland\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland_Brown\"}, {\"begin\": 988, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\", \"score\": 0.9940633023532677, \"rank\": 0.005972152510347306, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Examples include male chromosomes (XY) and genitalia that appears female (vulva) or female chromosomes (XX) and genitalia that appears male (penis).\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1188, \"end\": 1190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.851107990943221e-26, \"text\": \"XX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some people with DSDs have characteristics of both sexes.\\\"\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But if it is true that Khelif has DSD, that still does not answer the question.\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\", \"score\": 0.9940633023532677, \"rank\": 0.005972152510347306, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As far as we know, the boxer could be a male with DSD.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1423, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\", \"score\": 0.9940633023532677, \"rank\": 0.005972152510347306, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The XY chromosomes, and how they impact an individual's development, personality, physical characteristics and so on, are what matters.\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1433, \"end\": 1447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Bach does not seem to think so.\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1570, \"end\": 1574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999811784621, \"rank\": 1.882147962648599e-08, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bach's International Olympic Committee has faced some pretty intense backlash since clips of Khelif and Lin beating down their noticeably more feminine opponents began making their way onto the internet.\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999811784621, \"rank\": 1.882147962648599e-08, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who doubt the two finalists' feminine identities want them out of the Olympics, and those who are not sure want the IOC to force them to take a definitive chromosomal test.\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1930, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.113758946234429e-21, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One reporter pressed Bach on whether the committee would be introducing such a test - one that proves the sex of the athletes - and he responded by suggesting that no such test exists.\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2009, \"end\": 2013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999811784621, \"rank\": 1.882147962648599e-08, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If somebody is presenting us a scientifically solid system how to identify men and women, we are the first ones to do it,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2178, \"to\": 2310, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We do not like this uncertainty.\\\"\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The pro-LGBT brain rot has seemingly made its way all the way to the world Olympics.\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2431, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No matter what any blue-haired gender studies major tells you (they likely told Bach anyway), chromosomes are the most accurate way to tell a person's sex.\", \"from\": 2433, \"to\": 2588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999811784621, \"rank\": 1.882147962648599e-08, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some in the LGBT community have suggested otherwise by citing the existence of intersex individuals but, as one2002report shows, the prevalence of intersex individuals has been greatly exaggerated.\", \"from\": 2590, \"to\": 2787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2602, \"end\": 2606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9999831103580846, \"rank\": 1.660101628208381e-05, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trending:WATCH: No-Nonsense Judge TORCHES Violent Teen Robber and Gives Him a Harsh Sentence, Causing Thug's Family to Completely Lose It  According to the report, roughly 0.018 percent of individuals are \\\"intersex.\\\"\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 3005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The left would love for this vague, incredibly rare condition to be used as a loophole for transgender males to make their way into women's sports.\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And Bach seems more than happy to open the door for them.\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3160, \"end\": 3164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999811784621, \"rank\": 1.882147962648599e-08, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This article appeared originally onThe Western Journal.\", \"from\": 3215, \"to\": 3270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3254, \"end\": 3261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.99975120087591, \"rank\": 0.00024886101204520475, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You canemail Michael Austin, The Western Journal here, andread more of Michael Austin, The Western Journal's articles here.\", \"from\": 3272, \"to\": 3395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3293, \"end\": 3299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St